time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Two-pointer technique is used to efficiently reverse the letters in the string while keeping non-letter characters in place. The solution iterates through the string once, resulting in linear time complexity. The space complexity is also linear due to the conversion of the string to a character array. 
